The paper deals with a geometric optimization problem of finding an annulus with maximum width that avoids a given set of points in the plane. This problem is related to computational geometry and combinatorial optimization, which are covered by cs.CG and cs.DM. The algorithms presented in the paper involve data structures and geometric techniques, which are also relevant to cs.DS. The problem of finding an optimal location of a facility among input points is related to game theory, which is covered by cs.GT. Finally, the paper involves the analysis of algorithms and complexity, which are relevant to cs.CC.
